thread.title: Sydney council rejects WestConnex tunnel

title: Sydney council rejects WestConnex tunnel
text:
Sun, Feb 26, 2017, 10:56 AM AEDT - Australia Markets closed Sydney council rejects WestConnex tunnel AAP â€“ 1 hour 15 minutes ago Recommend Print 
A Sydney council has rejected proposed tunnelling sites for the controversial WestConnex project because it will increase traffic near a high school. 
A report to be released by the Inner West Council, which covers Lilyfield and Leichhardt, has raised significant concerns including social and environmental impacts of the proposed tunnels in those areas. 
It looked at the impact on 'dive' sites between the tunnel portals at Haberfield and the Rozelle Railyards. 
One of them is near a Leichhardt high school campus and the adjacent State Transit bus depot. 
The report raises traffic concerns saying it will increase the number of heavy trucks moving around an already-congested area. 
Locals have also complained about noise and dust. 
"As a town planner myself, I know that you look to exclude heavy engineering construction sites .... from locations close to sensitive land uses," the council's administrator Richard Pearson said in a statement. 
"I would have thought a school for almost 1000 students would fit that bill".
